WEBVTT

00:00.800 --> 00:04.400
Welcome to DHSI. Believe me, I wish I were there.

00:05.400 --> 00:07.200
Maybe we should play music here. I could add MIDI right now.

00:07.200 --> 00:08.000
[record scratch]

00:08.000 --> 00:09.800
[chiptune music] Get off the chatbot.

00:11.700 --> 00:14.200
Copilot is for entertainment purposes only.

00:13.900 --> 00:14.700
Slop.

00:14.700 --> 00:16.300
Chocolate-covered broccoli.

00:16.400 --> 00:18.400
[broccoli intensifies]

00:22.500 --> 00:25.400
Git is basically a time machine for your agents.

00:27.000 --> 00:28.900
YOLO mode. YOLO mode.

00:30.200 --> 00:33.000
This is not Windows. Things do not go to the recycling bin.

00:34.000 --> 00:35.500
[emergency broadcast tone]

00:35.700 --> 00:39.500
Breaking news. Anthropic has launched Fable 5. In the middle of class.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.700
Screw you, Anthropic.

00:42.200 --> 00:45.300
A Mythos-class model, made safe for general use.

00:45.700 --> 00:48.700
Everyone in the world is now updating their Claude Code.

00:47.500 --> 00:50.000
[alarm]

00:51.300 --> 00:54.000
(slowed) We're done. We're all done.

00:54.800 --> 00:56.200
Very Apple.

00:58.800 --> 01:03.000
You're basically waking up. You have amnesia. This is someone else's computer.

01:03.100 --> 01:05.100
In this exercise, we are Claude Code.

01:05.200 --> 01:09.000
I'll be back. I'll be back. I'll be back. (rising in pitch)

01:15.800 --> 01:18.400
The LLM didn't know how to press the gas.

01:18.200 --> 01:19.800
[engine sputters and dies]

01:23.300 --> 01:25.200
Don't launch OpenClaw. For God's sake.

01:25.200 --> 01:26.200
Open- Open- OpenClaw.

01:26.300 --> 01:28.500
I know kung fu. That's skills.

01:35.800 --> 01:37.800
Be careful what you prompt for.

01:38.400 --> 01:40.200
Did you do the right job?

01:40.400 --> 01:41.700
Of course I did.

01:41.800 --> 01:43.000
Of course I did. (higher)

01:43.000 --> 01:44.200
Of-of-of course I did.

01:44.300 --> 01:46.400
(slowed) OF COURSE I DID.

01:46.600 --> 01:48.400
Show me the evidence.

01:50.600 --> 01:52.000
All six findings fixed and verified.

01:52.300 --> 01:54.000
Day five. Demo day.

01:56.300 --> 01:58.300
A bluetooth scanner!

02:00.100 --> 02:02.100
Evil I!

02:03.900 --> 02:05.900
Penny Runner!

02:07.800 --> 02:09.800
Ed tech transparency!

02:11.600 --> 02:13.600
Smash the patriarchy!

02:15.400 --> 02:17.600
Feminist theory, into practice!

02:19.200 --> 02:21.400
A local patent database!

02:23.000 --> 02:25.000
Archive prep tools!

02:26.900 --> 02:28.900
A python cat game!

02:30.600 --> 02:32.800
All built in one week. By humanists.

02:32.900 --> 02:35.400
We have gotten to the promised land.

02:36.200 --> 02:39.200
I hope you all have great plans for Montreal tonight.

02:39.200 --> 02:43.200
Tokens. Tokens. Tokens. Tokens. (fading)

02:43.500 --> 02:45.000
[music fades]
